  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2432Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2432Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2432Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2432Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2432Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chips are cooking, slice your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>finely</p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and chop in half</p><p>Shred<strong> half</strong> the<strong> lettuce </strong>finely</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining lettuce</strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706535830466-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706535830466-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706535830466-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706535830466-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1706535830466-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> in a medium bowl – this is your <strong>Cajun-style</strong> <strong>spice mix</strong></p><p>Remove <strong>half</strong> the <strong>spice mix</strong> and set aside for later in a small bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to the <strong>remaining spice mix</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>spiced cornflour</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to a plate and add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> to a small bowl</p>",
